cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the use of economic pressure to incentivize ISPs to remove Traffic Manipulating Boxes (TMBs) from the transit core of the Internet. As such, it falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the flow of traffic and cash between ISPs, which relates to information theory (cs.IT) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of TMBs on revenue, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
